Class SignedQuantity

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Number

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<SignedQuantity>
Direct Known Subclasses:
NonNegativeQuantity
public class SignedQuantity
extends PreciseValue<SignedQuantity>
A quantity (in shares of a security) that can be positive, negative, or zero.

Instrument quantities are typically non-negative. A SignedQuantity is useful because it makes it explicit that a quantity is allowed to be negative or zero, since that's not a common case.

See Also:
PreciseValue, Serialized Form
